\begin_body

\begin_layout Title
Problem setting and definitions 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The problem we address deals with a team of robots exploring an environment
 initially unknown.
 The aim of this work is to find out if some features of the environment
 can be exploited in order to improve the exploration performances.
 This exploration problem can be formally defined through a 4-ple ⟨
\begin_inset Formula $A,E,P_{0},T$
\end_inset

⟩ where:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is the set of robots used for the exploration;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

 is the environment to explore;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $P_{0}$
\end_inset

is a vector of the initial poses of the team;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 is the termination criteria.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This four elements characterize the instance of exploration problem we are
 addressing, while the solution of the problem consists in producing a map
 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 of the environment 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

.
 The map 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 consists in a 2D occupancy grid representing the areas of 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

.
 The center of each cell is characterized by its coordinates in the environment,
 provided as a vector 
\begin_inset Formula $(x_{c},y_{c})$
\end_inset

.
 Each cell contains a variable, whose value tells if that cell is clear,
 occupied by an obstacle or still unexplored.
 Clearly, the first two values refer only to already explored cells, while
 the third refer to those cells which are still not mapped by any robot
 of the team.
 In particular, a cell is clear if there are no obstacles in it, otherwise
 it is occupied.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Team configuration
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For each robot 
\begin_inset Formula $a\in A$
\end_inset

 what needs to be described 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Mapping
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Coordination
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Environment
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The environments analyzed in this thesis are indoor ones.
 
\end_layout

\end_body
